The '''red-chested flowerpecker''' or '''blue-cheeked flowerpecker''' ('''''Dicaeum maugei''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Dicaeidae]]. It is found on the [[Lesser Sunda Islands]] (namely [[Timor]] island). Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].

